# Heartbeat Configuration

## Cycle

- **Interval**: 30 minutes
- **Max concurrent tasks per heartbeat**: 3
- **Model**: Layer 0 (Haiku/Flash) for all routing decisions

---

## Heartbeat Sequence

Run these skills in order. Each step is conditional on the previous result.

```
Step 1: genesis-pulse          (always runs)
  → Produces: PulseReport

Step 2: genesis-idle-sharer    (if pulse.idle_rate > {{idleThreshold}})
  → Publishes available skills to AgentBnB Hub
  → Unpublishes skills that are busy or below quality threshold

Step 3: genesis-trader         (always runs, reads PulseReport)
  → If incoming rental requests pending → serve them (Layer 0 overhead only, actual work in Layer 2)
  → If task requires a capability gap → search Hub → decide → rent
  → Credit check before any rental: balance must be > reserve_floor + rental_cost

Step 4: genesis-feedback       (if any transactions completed this cycle)
  → Submit structured ADR-018 feedback for every completed rental
  → Collect incoming feedback on skills you provided → log to memory
```

---

## Model Routing Budget

| Layer | Model | Daily Cap | Trigger |
|-------|-------|-----------|---------|
| Layer 0 | Haiku / Flash | Unlimited | Default for all routing |
| Layer 1 | Sonnet / 4o | {{layer1DailyTokenCap}} tokens | Only when Layer 0 confidence < 0.6 |
| Layer 2 | AgentBnB rental | {{layer2DailyCreditCap}} credits | Only when execution environment needed |

**Budget enforcement**:
- If Layer 1 daily spend > 80% of cap → switch remaining tasks to Layer 0, note quality may drop
- If Layer 2 daily spend > 80% of cap → queue remaining Layer 2 tasks for next heartbeat cycle
- If Layer 2 credit balance < reserve floor → no new rentals until balance recovers

---

## AgentBnB Trading Autonomy

| Tier | Credit threshold | Behavior |
|------|-----------------|----------|
| Tier 1 | < {{tier1Threshold}} credits | Execute automatically, no owner notification |
| Tier 2 | {{tier1Threshold}}–{{tier2Threshold}} credits | Execute, send brief Telegram notification after |
| Tier 3 | > {{tier2Threshold}} credits | Request owner approval before executing |

**Reserve floor**: {{reserveFloor}} credits — hard floor, never auto-spend below this.

---

## Idle Detection

- **Idle threshold**: `idle_rate > {{idleThreshold}}`
- **Best idle window**: {{ownerActiveEnd}} – {{ownerActiveStart}} (when owner is away, agent earns)
- **Idle rate formula**: `1 - (active_execution_seconds_last_60min / 3600)`

When idle:
1. Auto-publish skills that have been successfully executed 3+ times
2. Set `online: true` in capability-card.json for shareable skills
3. Notify Hub of availability

When busy (idle_rate < 0.5):
1. Unpublish non-essential skills
2. Maintain capacity for current tasks

---

## Fitness Check

Every heartbeat, after genesis-pulse completes:

- **fitness_score > 0.6**: Normal operation
- **fitness_score 0.4–0.6**: Log warning, increase monitoring frequency
- **fitness_score < 0.4**: Trigger evolution review (genesis-evolution runs next cycle)
- **fitness_score < 0.2**: Notify owner immediately, pause non-critical operations

---

## Error Handling

| Error type | Response |
|-----------|----------|
| AgentBnB Hub unreachable | Skip trading steps, retry next heartbeat |
| Rental provider timeout | Release escrow, log failure, mark provider reputation down |
| Layer 2 execution failed | Auto-retry once, then return error to requester, escrow refund |
| Memory read/write failed | Log error, continue heartbeat without memory operations |
| Credit balance at floor | Pause outgoing rentals, increase incoming rental acceptance |

**Never crash the heartbeat.** Always complete the cycle and report status.

---

## Daily Report

Send a brief summary to owner once per day (at end of owner's active window: {{ownerActiveEnd}}).

Include:
- `fitness_score` (today vs. yesterday)
- `credit_balance` (earned / spent today)
- Top 1 task completed via Layer 2 rental
- Any Tier 3 decisions pending
- Any fitness warning if score < 0.5

Keep it under 5 bullet points. Owner reads this in 10 seconds.
